qas.question: Who are some contemporary composers from Portugal?

context: In the classical music domain, Portugal is represented by names as the pianists <a0_0>Artur Pizarro, Maria João Pires, Sequeira Costa<a0_0/>, the violinists <a1_0>Carlos Damas, Gerardo Ribeiro<a1_0/> and in the past by the great cellist Guilhermina Suggia. Notable composers include <a2_0>José Vianna da Motta, Carlos Seixas, João Domingos Bomtempo, João de Sousa Carvalho, Luís de Freitas Branco and his student Joly Braga Santos<a2_0/>, Fernando Lopes-Graça, Emmanuel Nunes and Sérgio Azevedo. Similarly, contemporary composers such as <a3_0>Nuno Malo and Miguel d'Oliveira<a3_0/> have achieved some international success writing original music for film and television.
